
<!-- XML: W3Schools - XQuery Tutorial -->
<!-- Section 2: Example -->

<!-- We use books.xml for these examples. -->
<!-- XQuery uses functions to extract data from XML documents. -->

<!-- The doc() function is used to open the "books.xml" file: -->
doc("books.xml") 

<!-- XQuery uses path expressions to navigate through elements in an XML document. -->
<!-- The following path expression is used to select all the title elements in the "books.xml" file: -->
doc("books.xml")/bookstore/book/title

<!-- We can use predicates to select books with specific properties: -->
doc("books.xml")/bookstore/book[price<30]
